caption: Just might be the best Nashville Hot chicken sandwich I've ever had! Possibly the best in Chicago! Incredibly juicy and delicious. My 3rd delivery from here in two months and only gets better. Oh and the Bacon and Parm Mac and Cheese is 🔥
One of the best burgers in the city!
Great food

Got some delivery from them and it was great. Reasonable delivery times. The food was delivery hot and fresh and super delicious. I got shrimp po' boys with some regular fries and some truffle fries. Both were very delicious. Totally make sure to check them out. The shrimp in the po' boys were cooked to perfection and they weren't small either, which was nice.

I ordered the nashville hot chicken sandwich, the cuban, and a bunch of salads.  Sandwiches were amazing. Nashville was spicy and flavorful, the cuban had amazing pork belly and sauce. Salads were also VERY good.
We ordered the smoked gouda burger and the Nashville fried chicken sandwich and both were delicious!!! Also ordered some cheese curds and those were good too. Will order again soon!
Food was amazing and super timely service! Can’t wait to try more of their menu. :)
Food was great. Burgers cooked to perfection. The crew was super friendly and accommodating. Skip the delivery apps and order direct from the restaurant.
The food is so delicious, fresh, and has evenly balanced ingredients. The pesto pasta salad was incredible and so was the California Club. Will be ordering again!

Would love to give this place more positivity, except they are nothing but hateful and negative.   Food is great as long as you’re willing to put up with intolerant and atrocious customer service.  Got a run around for five minutes on the phone about how I, MYSELF, screwed up on the order after I inquired about sauce I requested and a mis charge for an item that was not available (??).  And if I wanted the extra sauce I should have paid for it.  Absolutely terrible customer service and the only reason I’d ever return is because the food is so good, maybe a little redemption available.   Step your front counter service up, or the jig is up cause we will black ball you for that kind of service.

Bluebird is one of my most favorite food places in Chicago.  The food is consistently fresh and amazing, staff is wonderful, and they have a cute dining area. COVID has made things weird (no dining in) but when I call to place an order for pickup it’s ready in 15-20 minutes.  I’m obsessed with the California Club (make sure to get it on a baguette)! The way all of the flavors/textures of this sandwich come together is pure magic. Their truffle fries are delicious and don’t get me started on the cheese curds - super tasty and you get a good sized portion for the price!
My favorite chicken sandwich in lakeview. So incredibly good. And their sides are also 10/10. Never have I had pasta salad this good. Can't stop recommending this place to friends
Amazing fries and burgers one of the best cheese steaks around.
The Bacon jam burger was yummy. And the Truffle and Duck Fat fries are killer!

Just ordered delivery from here for the first time even though I have walked past many times. Boy do I regret not going sooner. The truffle burger was amazing and the elotes are the best I ever had (by far). Will definitely be ordering again soon!

Okay meal but wouldn’t go back again. Ordered a chicken sandwich, Nashville hot and mac and cheese. Mac was my least favorite, lacked flavor and that good cheese pull. My bf thought it was good tho so. Chicken sandwich was okay, popeyes is better. Nashville hot (pictured) also okay, bun was too big for the piece of chicken. There were many bites of pure bread and coleslaw. Heard lots good words but was disappointed.  Warning: charge extra for sauces like ketchup and aloli

Discovered this place during Quarantine through delivery app...I am in love! The food is just fantastic. I have ordered multiple times and look forward to dining in. I absolutely recommend this place! So good!

I’ve never been to Bluebird in person, but this has been my quarantine go-to spot. Seriously the smoked Gouda burger might be my favorite burger ever. The portions are big, and the $5 Mac and cheese is so so yummy. Love this spot!
Some of the best burgers in Chicago. Along Kuma's is a must visit.  Variety of sauces, aioli to go with their friends is unsurpassable.  Great selection of sides
Chicken pesto sandwich and the Bluebird are amazing. You’ll remember this place after eating either of them

A lovely little place in Lakeveiw East! I live a few blocks away so I frequently get takeout from here. The service is always efficient and the staff have always been delightful! I typically get the chicken sandwich and a salad, but the elote side is also a favorite from here as well.
Everything's excellent! I get the food as take out and it's always sooo good!  The cheese fries and the Mac and cheese are my favourites 🤤🤤

My favorite Nashville hot fried chicken sandwich.  I get one often when I'm in Lakeview.  You have to ask for it extra hot because the standard is for people afraid of spice,  but it's juicy and so well seasoned

I went to this place based on the above average ratings and had high expectations unfortunately the meal ended up to be very low expectations in terms of the quality of the food itself and the actual customer service guy with the dreadlocks at the front desk was extremely rude it’s just basic questions I had it seems like I was bothering him by asking so I will not be going back to this place
username: JM JM JM JM JM JM

caption: *this review is based on delivery due to COVID-19*  My boyfriend and I were craving fried chicken sandwiches and checked reviews for several spots, ultimately we decided on Bluebird and we were SO happy with the results!  I got the Nashville hot and although it wasn’t as hot as I was hoping, it tasted incredible and had a great heat to it! The chicken was juicy but still had that delicious fried crunch to it. My bf got the OG fried chicken sandwich and his was equally as juicy, crispy and delicious!  We also ordered the truffle fries and duck fat fries and wow...just wow. So they came soggy, which we figured, but when we popped them in our toaster over for a few mins at 425 they crisped right up and the flavor was everything, especially the truffle fries. Duck fat fries definitely tasted like the crispy skin on a chicken and it was tasty! Will definitely order from here again!

We've walked past Bluebird a lot, and only just got around to checking it out. We are so glad we did! We each got a burger (the truffle burger and the Big Texas Juanita) and both were DELICIOUS. The truffle fries were also amazing. We got takeout, but it seems like it has a fun vibe, so we'll definitely be trying dine in once the quarantine is over. There is so much more on the menu that piqued our interest, so we can't wait to go back.

German bird was legit. Dijonaise (usually not a fan of mayo or Dijon alone, but I’m trying to grow as a person) was great and not grossly piled on like on other chicken sandwiches. The Chicken was fried great and the flavor profiles here were tasty.  Cheese fries were good, but the bacon bits on top tasted artificial. I mean, I still inhaled it, but actual bacon would’ve been amazing.
My favorite chicken sandwich spot in Chicago! So good, and always get great customer service. 100% recommend for anyone who hasn't tried!
Great sandwiches and sides. Loved the Chicken pesto
Really good restaurant. Staff always friendly and kind.

I ordered from here a couple of times through DoorDash and my goodness I fell in love with the California club! I ordered from there through delivery a couple of times and I just kept telling myself that I have to come to the location to try it out.  Today I stopped by the location in person for the first time. You walk in, very cozy and friendly place. I was there 15 minutes after opening so there was only two staffs working at the time but they were friendly. I sat down, made my order at the cash register. Price was almost $20 cause I also ordered an uncle john tallboy.  Would come back here again for a casual quick chat and snack.
Amazing duck fat fries and the Juanita burger!!!

Such an underrated spot. Some of the best burgers and chicken sandwiches in town, not to mention the sides are creative and fantastic. Duck fat fries are also a must try (especially if you are ordering in. They travel really well)

The menu is fantastic when prepared correctly. The quality varies wildly from being perfect to sometimes rotten. My partner and I love their bacon jam burger (borderline obsessed), both fried chicken sandwiches, and the duck fat fries with mustard miso butter. Those items keep us coming back for more. Half the time the food is amazing but the rest of the time the cooks seem to throw it together like they don't care at all. It is a huge gamble that often ends in disappointment. Slowly we are stopping trying to get good food from there all together. The biggest issues are with the sides and forgotten sauces and drinks. We do order from Postmates but that is not the issue. At times the elotes can be wet and almost soupy or other times dry from too much powdered cheese and not spicy at all. The cole slaw can also either be extremely watery or basically dry cabbage with pepper. I recently got a salad with rotten lettuce all over the bottom. Not wilted from the chicken but yellow, brown, slimy, and rotten. Their flavors are top notch but they need to get their cooks to follow the same recipes or we will not be coming back, which is extremely saddening because we loved them at one point. Take your chances but don't get your hopes up.
Great food, great music. Can't beat it! They had some pretty cool plants too. I loved how many iPads they had - it makes them look very rich.

Decided to try 2 burgers here: the Nashville Hot and the Smoked Gouda Burger. I wanted to start off by complimenting  the staff, I do not eat bacon and didn't notice one of the burgers had it. Once I received the burger I asked the staff if they could make me a new one and the gladly did even though it was completely my fault for not being fully attentive to the menu description. In terms of the food, the Nashville burger was phenomenal, as was the Gouda Burger. Truffle fries and fried pickles were also very good. 100% would recommend!!
Waste of time !
Love!

I ordered the Gouda burger on 11.19.19 along with duck fries. I picked up my order, took it back with me and then as soon as i cut into it i saw that my burger was still raw, bright pink. I called and told bluebird and they said they would have another burger ready in about 10 minutes. 10 minutes is a very short time to cook a burger all the way through that was my estimated wait time before.  I go back to pick it up take it back and cut into it again and ITS STILL RAW. I literally re-cooked the burger myself on my own time. In my order I wanted two sauces and those were forgotten about as well (they usually forget everytime) I'm glad that i caught this instead of eating it and getting really sick. I probably will not be coming back here. Please cut into your food before eating here!!!!!

I’m currently trapped in my hotel room in Chicago with my 13 month old because the weather is awful. I ordered from Bluebirds through DoorDash and it did not disappoint. The Nashville hot hot hot is the best chicken sandwich I’ve ever had and my baby is loving the truffle fries. Definitely a great find and good prices.
The truffle fries - BEST IVE HAD, and I’ve had my share of truffles fries...  I didn’t like the chicken sandwich. I was very disappointed. It was chewy and “vein-ee”

Thank you for a Keto friendly menu. My goodness I was pleasantly surprised at how fulfilling and delicious it would be. I ordered the California Club not bun. My first bite made me thank Jesus! I bite into crunchy bacon 🥓 avocado 🥑 and beautifully seasoned chicken 🍗  with some type of sauce that accompanied it perfectly. Then I got to taste the lemon 🍋 pepper wet hot wings with their homemade chunky blue cheese. Let’s just say I ordered and extra to go.  I am truly grateful I found this place on yelp. The owner and staff are welcoming and friendly as well. Stop by and see for yourself.
Bugs were flying around, bathrooms were dirty, and service was pretty slow.
Thank you!! Great customer service and owners!
Smoked gouda burger and Nashville sandwich are some of the best my husband and I have ever had!

ordered the fried chicken sandwich and truffle fries and both were very subpar. truffle fries tasted rather stale and the sandwich was no better than you can get at fast food places. the worst part of the meal was what happened the next day 🤢

I only come here for the Impossible Bluebird  Burger so cannot comment on any other food items. It's a tiny spot with just a couple of bar style seats by the window but their service has always been amazingly friendly which for some reason surprises me every time. It's not healthy food but it's a fun treat every now and then.

Really enjoyed our visit to Bluebird. The two burgers we ordered (truffle burger and bacon jam burger) were excellent and our side of truffle fried did not disappoint. It’s a cool & casual spot with a nice selection of drinks and all the burger, sandwich, and salad options you could need. Go here.
Great spot with excellent chicken sandwiches and sides!! I have dined in and ordered out! All times have been excellent! Keep up the good work! Can’t get a great chicken sandwich everywhere!!
Chicken sandwiches are top notch. 👍
The hot hot hot burger was really amazing
Misleading reviews. Horrible customer service and food was not good at all. It left me and my family sick and forced us to the clinic down the street.
Absolutely awesome low key location. The Bluebird Burger was awesome!
There was plastic in my food.
Excellent sandwiches and salads! Most could probably be shared they are so huge. Highly recommend!
Food poisoning, ordered Truffle Burger and Truffle Mac and Cheese, burger was slightly on the rare side; however I ordered medium.
Love the food, service and great atmosphere !
Try the bluebird sandwich... Awesome. Cheese fries are great too, plus friendly staff.

Good neighborhood find! We tried the fried chicken sandwich called Bluebird with duck fries and truffle Mac and cheese. The portions are very generous and everything was super tasty. Definitely come hungry!!
Lovely, casual, simply great food
Awesome food and people!
The Gouda burger and the duck fat fries are my go to.

Service was friendly, food was reasonably priced for Chicago, and everything was absolutely delicious. I’m on keto, and I got the cheeseburger with a fried egg on it. Absolute perfection.  GET THE FRIED EGG. Seriously.

Got the hot hot Nashville chicken. It was delicious but not that hot. Will try the hot hot hot next. The hot hot was a lingering 4/10 on the hotness scale. But delicious. Quality ingredients. The guy at the counter was good people. Will come again. 2 people was like 25 bucks which is not bad at all.
The burger was okay, make sure you ask for it well done if you're not a fan of medium rare beef burgers. I did however really enjoyed the truffle fries and Mac and cheese.

Great service and great food. Prices were 10 to 12 per person and sizes were more than enough for the money. Hot chicken does not mess around. Salads are fresh and large and the shrimp po boy was amazing. Will be coming back.  Deserves every one of the 5 stars.

The best food in the area that only a few know about. My kind of spot. Had the Nashville hot and it was delishious. Sandwich came out hot, food tasted fresh and unique, and restaurant was very clean. Not fancy but just right. The chef even came out after and asked how our food was. We notice the small things and appreciate the extra effort. Highly recommended.
Good fresh food. Big portions! Had the chicken pesto sandwich and duck fat fries. Delicious! Definitely going back to try a burger .
Good eats and nice location. Life isn't about counting calories - live in the moment and eat what tastes right...
Great sandwich and burgers. But buy the alcohol you advertise
It was great customer service.  Super friendly.  Quick to make our food.  Food was great! I would recommend highly.
German bird
Delicious food and calm comforting atmosphere. Kid friendly too. We'll be coming again!

It was so good! Ordered the fried chicken sandwich and truffle fries. Both were excellent. Nice clean atmosphere inside. Would give 5 stars but the heavy metal music that was playing was very annoying. Will be going back for the good food though :)
Food took awhile to come to our table but hot damn I think that was the best buffalo chicken sandwich I’ve ever had in my life
I ordered from here through DoorDash. They told DoorDash i cancelled my order twice.... 3 hours and $70 later we still had no food. What a joke.

My sister just went to this restaurant. She bought back a Smoked Gouda Burger and Truffle fries for me. The fries were excellent but the burger is from heaven. My goodness. I haven’t tasted anything like this before. So good!!! The burger meat was so smooth. Worth every dollar!!

Heard of this place from doordash. Was trying to get really good quality burgers from somewhere and this was the first place that popped up with really good reviews. I ordered the chicken sandwich for my boyfriend and a cheeseburger for myself. When I bit into my cheeseburger I noticed the inside of my burger WAS PINK and raw. I had already got into 7 bites until I realized my burger was undercooked. I notify doordash and I tried called bluebird and everytime I called I got a dead tone at the end. I got food poisoning and was throwing up repeatedly for the past 6 hours because of my undercooked meat. People should be aware and should be given an option for how you want your meat. Very disappointed with this place.
Love this place. Order all of the time! just ordered and can't wait til it arrives!!!

This is a quaint spot, friendly staff and good food. I had the Nashville Hot with truffle fries. So yummy. I got the second level of heat and it didn't disappoint. Begging for water, hahaha. The chicken was a nice portion and I was full by the end.
Pretty good burgers. Prices a tad high. Didn't appreciate the death metal that was playing for half of the sitting

Surprisingly good food.  This east Lakeview place flies completely under the internet's version of the Chicago food scene. The Gouda bacon jam burger was at least as good as DMK's. The Nashville hot chicken was also a solid sandwich. The duck fat fries were a very well executed and delicious basic fry. The beer list is pretty much the standard local craft beer list available everywhere these days. In my opinion the best reason to come here though is that it is a quiet, uncrowded and unhurried oasis.

If you’re looking for a quiet place to duck into for a bite, Bluebird is the place for you. I had a Smoked Gouda Burger which was really good! Bluebird is a small restaurant. Perfect if you’re looking for a quiet place to eat. The pricing is a little high but comparable to the restaurants in the area.
The burgers are tasty, juicy and full of flavor. The fries are hot and crispy. It didn't become soggy.
Yummy food. Took a while to get but it was worth it. Wasn’t very busy
How about a vegetarian sandwich?
really good burgers and salads at a couple bucks less than other places. It is clean, comfortable and the people are friendly.
One of the best fried chicken sandwiches in the city.
Nice restaurant! The store inside is clean. The guy at the order desk is nice. I love the Truffle Duck-fat burger. It is delicious!
Great little spot. Had the Nashville Hot and boy was it spicy. Not for the faint of heart, but worth every tear. Great beer and atmosphere
Amazing lunch! Great place with even better food. Choose the burger you fancy, but take it from me and try the Mac&Cheese at BlueBird.
Great food and nice staff!

Love this place. Wife's fav burger in Chicago. Never busy dine in (seems like steady take out). Service is a bit sloow but is friendly and attentive. No more byob :(... Still 5*. Chicken sandwich good and truffle fries AMAAZING!
Amazing food! Loved the Elotes the most!

I had the Nashville Hot Hot Hot Sandwich, and it's the best chicken sandwich I've ever had. The sauce was spicy but perfectly balanced by the slaw and pickles. I'm still thinking about it a day later, it was *that* good. I'm actually taking the time to review it on here to spread the news, it was *that* good.  Also had the duck fat fries, which were fine but soggy; this was all delivered, though, so I'm sure that wouldn't have been as big of a problem if they had been brought out fresh.
Good place to go. Nice setting
BEST BURGER IN CHICAGO!!!

Don't bother with this place. We used to order from here and they have gone down hill. They made a mistake on our order and when we called to ask them to fix it, they said "the owner will call you back in a minute." Ok... Why can't you take care of it? Why does the owner have to take care of it? We said ok, and waited. 15 minutes goes by (a long time when you're hungry) so we call back. "The owner will call you back in 5 minutes" 10 minutes goes by and no phone call. We call back again and ask why they can't just fix the order or do something about it. And they hung up on us. We got our refund in the end from the app, but what a nightmare to deal with this restaurant all for a simple fix on an order they made a mistake on... Not going back again.

Visiting Chicago from London to see a band, I came across this place. Having never tried a shrimp po boy, I wasn't sure what to expect. It was great! Shrimps were sweet and perfectly cooked, with the right amount of crunch. The bread was soft like a Vietnamese banh mi and the sauce / salad / pickle combo set it all off.  The place is cosy and the staff are friendly. Five stars!!
Quiet and simple vibe, but delicious food and quick service
The food is fantastic,  a neighborhood must no doubt!!
My new favorite sandwich stop in the city. Honestly can’t believe this place doesn’t have a line out the door at all times
Amazing burgers
It's hard to go wrong with a spicy friend chicken sandwich. Others at the table were not as satisfied with their orders.
Amazing burgers

I visited Chicago last Friday for the first time.  I was looking for a good place to eat lunch near where I was staying and came across Bluebird.  Service was great, food was even better.  Nice and comfy environment.  I got the bacon fries and a cheeseburger.  I barely finished it was so filling.  I do not regret my decision.
It's okay - more hype than substance.
Menu is on the pricier side, but the food is delicious and worth it! Great moden American takes on classic dishes.

The good is delish, quiet place to listen to music or have a conversation.  They can be rather overwhelmed during lunch time, do to a big carry out service, but you still feel attended and get good service.
Great laid back food Dining in worked great Tasty

I don't get some of these reviews. The food here is amazingly good and the prices are really fair considering the quality.  I get lunch from there once a week (takeout) and I have never had a bad sandwich and the people are truly friendly.
Great sandwiches
Great buffalo chicken salad
Love the burger and fries! Decent price for the neighborhood.
The Nashville Hot was delicious and a fantastic deal at just $8.95.
Great food, good service. Love the bright interior.
This place is joke .they take forever just to make sandwich. I will never go there again

Great sandwhiches and the best service. The person in charge here was really helpful. I had a great cheese steak and truffle fries with homemade ali-oli. Everything was great and I had half of it saved for later.
Food is ok. Definitely overpriced.
Vastly overpriced and the food was terrible quality!!
Just sandwich shop staples on the menu, but everything you'd expect from a fried chicken joint plus an extra helping of deliciousness.
The food was very good and the service was quick.

My wife and I tried this place for lunch while in town visiting family. We were excited to give it a try after looking at the reviews, and it surpassed our expectations. The bacon jam cheeseburger was the best burger I've ever had, and my wife's hot hot chicken sandwich was cooked expertly and spiced formidably. The duck fat fries, truffle mac, and the array of accompanying sauces were simply outstanding. Service was quick and friendly. This place will for sure be on our "must visit" list for next time.

Went here for lunch and ordered the gouda burger w/ truffle parmesan fries. EXCELLENT! Going back soon. Friendly and welcoming environment. A coworker has also gone tgree times already and loves it too.
Friendly, fast service. Loved the truffle Macaroni & Cheese.
I ordered a meal for delivery. Really good food and the duck fat fries are amazing. Thanks!
The chicken sandwich was amazing. The place byob so bring your own.
Great burger and big portions
Horrible customer service. Food isn't good enough to put up with the mistakes and lack of management. Will not eat here again.

Delicious food in an upscale counter-service style. I've visited twice, and intend on making myself a regular.  First visit, I had the shrimp po' boy and duck fat fries. Being from Maryland, I take seafood seriously, and when it's served in Chicago, I take it with a grain of salt. This exceeded my standards for sure. Giant shrimp and generous portions, all the flavors were on point.  Second visit, I had the Nashville hot. I was hesitant because I don't love spicy food, but this is a total winner. The chicken is outrageously juicy, and the spice is more flavorful than it is heat for the sake of heat. The slaw and pickles really round it out, and the buttery bun is better than Chick-fil-A.  To top it off, the service is friendly and enthusiastic. I wish these guys all the success in the world.
